## Prerequisites
- Python (>= 3.8)
- pip
- Git

## Setup Steps
- Clone the repository  
  `git clone https://github.com/your-username/emotion-detection-speech.git`  
  `cd emotion-detection-speech`

- Create virtual environment  
  `python -m venv venv`

- Activate virtual environment  
  - Windows: `venv\Scripts\activate`  
  - Mac/Linux: `source venv/bin/activate`

- Install dependencies  
  `pip install -r requirements.txt`

- Download datasets (RAVDESS, TESS)

- Place datasets in  
  `data/` folder

- Train the model (optional)  
  `python train.py`

- Run the project  
  `python main.py`

- Run web app (optional)  
  `streamlit run app.py`

## Notes
- Use `.wav` audio files
- Ensure correct dataset path
- Use GPU for faster training (optional)
